              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:εὐαγγελίζω&lt;SDBG:εὐαγγελίζω:000000&gt;} ‘to tell the good news,’ {D:33.215}) the content of good news (in the NT a reference to the gospel about Jesus)</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>the good news</Gloss>
                <Gloss>the gospel</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages the expression ‘the gospel’ or ‘the good news’ must be rendered by a phrase, for example, ‘news that makes one happy’ or ‘information that causes one joy’ or ‘words that bring smiles’ or ‘a message that causes the heart to be sweet.’</Comments>
